title: A Year to Remember 1933
brief_description: Collection of newsreel footage, which made up Australia’s history in 1933 - Kingsford-Smith arrives in Brisbane - Royal Navy destroyers - Gift from British Government - Discovery of gold in Australia, Los Angeles - Heavyweight boxer, Primo Carnera, fights kangaroo, Billycart racing at Bellevue Hill, Sydney - Fashions for women - Bondi Beach- Bodyline bowling creates controversy- Great trotting pacer Walla Walla… and much more. Rated: G
